<div class="alert alert-info mb-4" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading"><span class="bi bi-info-circle"></span> Form Validation Sample</h4>
    <p>
        This page demonstrates form validation using the <code>ObservableValidator</code> pattern from CommunityToolkit.Mvvm
        integrated with Blazor's built-in validation components.
    </p>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-check-circle"></span> Validation Features</h6>
            <ul class="small">
                <li><strong>Data Annotations:</strong> Use standard attributes like <code>[Required]</code>, <code>[EmailAddress]</code>, <code>[Phone]</code></li>
                <li><strong>MvvmObservableValidator:</strong> Component that integrates ViewModel validation with Blazor forms</li>
                <li><strong>ValidationSummary:</strong> Displays all validation errors in one place</li>
                <li><strong>ValidationMessage:</strong> Shows field-specific validation errors</li>
                <li><strong>HasErrors Property:</strong> Enables/disables submit button based on validation state</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-gear"></span> How It Works</h6>
            <p class="small">
                The ViewModel's Contact property inherits from <code>ObservableValidator</code>, which provides 
                automatic validation when property values change. The validation results are reflected 
                immediately in the UI through Blazor's validation components.
            </p>
            <p class="small">
                Try entering invalid data (empty fields, invalid email format, invalid phone format) 
                to see the real-time validation feedback. The Save button will be disabled until 
                all validation rules pass.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <p class="mb-0">
        <span class="bi bi-lightbulb"></span> <strong>Key Benefit:</strong> 
        Seamless integration between CommunityToolkit.Mvvm's validation and Blazor's form validation, 
        providing automatic UI updates and command integration with validation state.
    </p>
</div>
